00:07:54,173 --> 00:07:55,465
or eight miles this morning.

182
00:07:55,466 --> 00:07:57,076
- [Joe] And up and down mountains too.

183
00:07:57,082 --> 00:07:58,372
- Yeah, it's crazy.

184
00:07:58,373 --> 00:08:00,483
We had a discussion yesterday
while we were tracking him.

185
00:08:00,484 --> 00:08:03,478
Just looking at the
hooves, and you would think

186
00:08:03,479 --> 00:08:05,475
animal this size would have bigger hooves.

187
00:08:05,482 --> 00:08:06,492
- Yeah.
- But you saw the terrain

188
00:08:06,493 --> 00:08:07,542
that they run in.

189
00:08:07,543 --> 00:08:09,098
So it will be very difficult for him

190
00:08:09,099 --> 00:08:11,336
to move around here if the
hooves were any bigger.

191
00:08:11,338 --> 00:08:13,348
So the hooves are quite small actually

192
00:08:13,352 --> 00:08:15,622
for the size of animal, but
it is because of the terrain.

193
00:08:15,623 --> 00:08:17,719
- Yeah cause then when
I stopped and asked you,

194
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,207
you know what that track
was, you said, kudu,

195
00:08:20,212 --> 00:08:23,136
and I said, a small one,
and Douglas said no big.

196
00:08:23,137 --> 00:08:24,057
- [Leon] Yes.

197
00:08:24,058 --> 00:08:25,418
- And I thought oh wow really.

198
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:26,709
Cause I guess I was expecting--

199
00:08:26,710 --> 00:08:28,330
- Yeah because the other
thing that happened

200
00:08:28,331 --> 00:08:30,379
is that you saw us with oryx track,

201
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:32,445
and remember it looked a lot bigger.

202
00:08:32,446 --> 00:08:33,876
But the big thing is
what you must remember

203
00:08:33,877 --> 00:08:35,717
with the oryx that it's
a desert dwelling animal,

204
00:08:35,718 --> 00:08:38,257
but normally most of the
time they're in Namibia,

205
00:08:38,258 --> 00:08:39,626
they were introduced here.

206
00:08:39,632 --> 00:08:41,611
And the big thing is to walk in the sand,

207
00:08:41,612 --> 00:08:43,181
it's like deflating your car tires.

208
00:08:43,182 --> 00:08:45,529
So it will carry the
weight, and that's why

209
00:08:45,530 --> 00:08:47,190
there's a bigger hooves to just spread the

210
00:08:47,191 --> 00:08:49,275
weight over a bigger area.

211
00:08:49,284 --> 00:08:50,607
- That makes sense.

212
00:08:50,608 --> 00:08:52,238
But yeah you're right with all the rocks,

213
00:08:52,239 --> 00:08:54,299
they gotta step in between them.

214
00:08:54,301 --> 00:08:55,131
- [Leon] Yes.

215
00:08:55,134 --> 00:08:56,574
- Like we're supposed
to, but with my big feet

216
00:08:56,575 --> 00:08:58,780
I (laughing), I stumble.
- We stumble.

217
00:08:58,783 --> 00:09:00,301
We stumble sometimes.

218
00:09:00,302 --> 00:09:03,052
(dramatic music)

219
00:09:08,434 --> 00:09:09,834
- As it turns out that shot hit about

220
00:09:09,835 --> 00:09:14,240
two inches a little bit
forward on his shoulder,

221
00:09:14,241 --> 00:09:17,261
just a two inches back
he would of been down.

222
00:09:17,262 --> 00:09:19,510
So that was the difference between

223
00:09:19,511 --> 00:09:23,574
instant elation and finding that animal,

224
00:09:23,575 --> 00:09:28,235
and a night of worry, and
another whole day of tracking.

225
00:09:29,335 --> 00:09:31,705
And the work that we put in.

226
00:09:31,712 --> 00:09:33,372
I mean have all those people to thank,

227
00:09:33,373 --> 00:09:35,645
especially Douglas and Leon

228
00:09:35,651 --> 00:09:38,164
for their tracking and persistence.

229
00:09:38,165 --> 00:09:40,525
And Geoffery and his
crew that came out there.

230
00:09:40,528 --> 00:09:43,736
