00:10:21,591 --> 00:10:24,011
This is a vachellia tortilis.

245
00:10:25,021 --> 00:10:27,629
When they're young like this it just looks

246
00:10:27,630 --> 00:10:29,306
like a big bush, but if you scan over,

247
00:10:29,308 --> 00:10:30,608
if you look at this tree behind us.

248
00:10:30,614 --> 00:10:31,452
- Yep.

249
00:10:31,453 --> 00:10:32,797
- That's called an umbrella
tree because you know

250
00:10:32,802 --> 00:10:34,222
they come up and they spread open.

251
00:10:34,223 --> 00:10:35,390
That is nasty.

252
00:10:36,505 --> 00:10:38,925
I mean it got me right there.

253
00:10:38,930 --> 00:10:41,760
These leaves come off really easy.

254
00:10:43,044 --> 00:10:46,214
So what they do is if you have a look,

255
00:10:47,416 --> 00:10:50,166
when they're really young
they have a lot of these

256
00:10:50,171 --> 00:10:51,871
long white thorns to protect
them from over grazing,

257
00:10:51,872 --> 00:10:54,349
so they can reach adulthood.

258
00:10:54,352 --> 00:10:56,192
Yeah so this got softer thorn yet,

259
00:10:56,193 --> 00:10:58,161
