614
00:25:24,626 --> 00:25:26,026
why this is called Salt Lake.

615
00:25:26,027 --> 00:25:29,687
So back in the late
1800s when this area was

616
00:25:30,626 --> 00:25:33,526
first settled by the
British, and predominately

617
00:25:33,531 --> 00:25:35,461
the Dougmore family.

618
00:25:35,463 --> 00:25:38,633
They found a large salt deposits here.

619
00:25:40,061 --> 00:25:43,760
Animals licking the soil,
and they actually sank water

620
00:25:43,761 --> 00:25:47,287
wells down here for
water for their cattle.

621
00:25:47,288 --> 00:25:49,848
But it was too saline to do anything with.

622
00:25:49,851 --> 00:25:53,601
And, you know, over the
centuries people have

623
00:25:54,475 --> 00:25:58,225
mostly used sea water
to evaporation for salt

624
00:25:59,383 --> 00:26:02,803
or natural salt deposits, or salt mining.

625
00:26:04,192 --> 00:26:07,432
And what they do here is
actual solely evaporation.

626
00:26:07,433 --> 00:26:09,975
So if you have a look over there,

627
00:26:09,976 --> 00:26:12,726
there's these squared pond like things,

628
00:26:12,729 --> 00:26:14,089
and they actually pump the water out

629
00:26:14,092 --> 00:26:17,289
from underground, and pump it in there

630
00:26:17,290 --> 00:26:19,230
and evaporate over a few weeks,

631
00:26:19,233 --> 00:26:21,242
and then it crystallizes.

632
00:26:21,243 --> 00:26:22,732
- It's that salty?

633
00:26:22,733 --> 00:26:24,046
- It's that salty.

634
00:26:24,047 --> 00:26:27,717
So the water that's
underneath us right here

635
00:26:27,722 --> 00:26:30,752
actually has between,
depending on rainfall,

636
00:26:30,753 --> 00:26:33,593
between a 67 to 85% solidity.

637
00:26:35,026 --> 00:26:39,406
And salt starts crystallizing
in the mid to high 90s.

638
00:26:39,408 --> 00:26:42,348
And that just shows
you how difficult it is

639
00:26:42,353 --> 00:26:44,193
to make sea salt, because
sea salt's actually

